This paper deals with a static complexity analysis for a higher-order functional language, which is a topic typically studied in the programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-categories. The use of structural list recursion suggests a focus on data structures (cs.DS) and the potential for analyzing algorithms. The formalization of the proof in Coq suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and formal methods (cs.FL).
